"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. Joel Salatin is uh my favorite author other than Albert Howard in the whole regenerative agriculture scene. I've read a bunch of his books. Uh the first book that I read in this whole venture was You Can Farm. I have no idea why I read it. I'm just a city kid. I've I never even grew up with a garden. And much less any sort of agricultural anything. And I read You Can Farm and it enthralled me. I was immediately trying to make compost piles. It's not just about farming, it's not just about how to become a farmer. It's about the techniques of farming, what what you're trying to do with regenerative agriculture, the law of returns, where you're you're replenishing the soils with a carbon and nitrogen bonding process that you initiate that you cultivate. In his case, he has a lot of cows that help him do it. He has a winter period where he just sits and makes uh great compost out of his manure and just keeps adding wood chips and lets pigs go through it after the season to break it up. And at the end of it, he's got very high quality mulch compost that he spreads out over his field and regenerates and creates a huge carbon capture through that, which is accumulating into his soil. I think he has 10% over 30 years of accumulation from what was probably very, very slim pickings before he started. And that's a tremendous feat uh getting those kinds of percentages while actively rotating and having an active cattle operation where you're selling livestock and doing it very successfully. You know, that he's such a wonderful model because this is how regenerative agriculture could work. A lot of it's marketing, a lot of it's him going after, and a lot of the the book You Can Farm is about how to market and about how to think about your customers. Oh, the book is so great. Anyway, uh that's I wanted to give a shout out to Joel Salatin because he's one of my favorites. I don't mention as much. I'm always talking about Albert Howard. Um but I have five copies of You Can Farm just to give away. It gives you any idea how much I love that book. Uh anyway, just wanted to make a video about how much I like that guy. Thanks.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.88,\n      \"end\": 3.12,\n      \"duration\": 2.24,\n      \"confidence\": 0.984,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.88,\n          \"end\": 1.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.992\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 1.12,\n          \"end\": 1.28,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 1.44,\n          \"end\": 1.6,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 1.6,\n          \"end\": 1.92,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 1.92,\n          \"end\": 2.24,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \".\",\n          \"start\": 2.8,\n          \"end\": 3.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 0.919\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Joel Salatin is uh my favorite author other than Albert Howard in the whole regenerative agriculture scene.\",\n      \"start\": 3.12,\n      \"end\": 12.56,\n      \"duration\": 9.44,\n      \"confidence\": 0.994,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Jo\",\n          \"start\": 3.12,\n          \"end\": 3.44,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"el\",\n          \"start\": 3.44,\n          \"end\": 3.76,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n